1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,560
- Mika.
- Hey.

2
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:44,960
- Hey, Pakbung, stop.
- Stop!

3
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:47,840
You can't take care of Pakbung,
just like you couldn't take care of Dad.

4
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:50,040
You can't take care of anyone, Trai.

5
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:52,560
I think we should reconsider
our relationship status.

6
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:53,720
Pakbung.

7
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:00,400
Pakbung! You just love sticking your nose
where it doesn't belong.

8
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:08,600
You bastard!

9
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:10,880
I'm the reason…

10
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:13,000
<i>that Dad died.</i>

11
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,160
How close are you to Rut?

12
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:17,840
You'd be charged as an accomplice
to attempted murder.

13
00:03:17,920 --> 00:03:19,920
<i>Do you think</i>
<i>something this small can touch me?</i>

14
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,560
Watch yourself.

15
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:22,720
If you even can.

16
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,400
You're with Pakbung,
but where's your mind?

17
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:25,360
What are you talking about?

18
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:28,480
- Pakbung.
- Pakbung.

19
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:30,040
<i>You're out of chances now, Trai.</i>

20
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:44,600
Mr. Rachen.

21
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:47,920
Honestly, I'm not hurt that badly.

22
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:50,840
I'm not Trai.
You don't have to put up a front with me.

23
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:52,840
You care about him. I get that.

24
00:03:52,920 --> 00:03:55,320
But don't love him
more than you love yourself.

25
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:57,120
I don't like that.

26
00:03:57,200 --> 00:04:00,520
We survived. We even caught the criminal.

27
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:03,400
At a time like this, we should be
celebrating more than anything.

28
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:06,000
Please don't be angry at Mr. Trai.

29
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:36,600
- It's my fault.
- No need to tell me that.

30
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:38,320
Everything. Uncle Rat, Dad,

31
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:41,440
and the culprit.
Was Rut really acting alone?

32
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:43,280
Was Mrs. Mookmanee involved too?

33
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:46,120
It's overwhelming in my head.

34
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:49,640
Do you think you're the only one
thinking about this? I'm thinking too.

35
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:52,960
But you're so caught up in it that
you forget to care about other people.

36
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:54,840
You have to know how to separate things.

37
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:56,440
You remember back then?

38
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:59,160
You were biased against Dad
and the company, and what happened?

39
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:01,520
You forgot to think about others,
and what happened?

40
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,720
How many people got hurt because of you?
Do you remember?

41
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,640
You want to go back
to being like that again?

42
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:08,520
Wow, Bro.

43
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:12,960
You're not even giving me
a moment for remorse?

44
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:15,200
This is me giving you space.
Do you feel remorse yet?

45
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,520
I do.

46
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:21,800
Thank you for waking me up.

47
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:23,360
Listen to me.

48
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:25,800
I'm telling you this clearly.

49
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:29,720
If you can't take care of Pakbung,
or can't do better than I can,

50
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:33,560
then I'll be the one
who takes care of her myself.

51
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,400
Hey! Mr. Trai?

52
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,360
How did you get in here?

53
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:11,600
Hey! Hey!

54
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:12,920
What are you doing?

55
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:15,840
Why didn't you complain like this
when Rachen carried you?

56
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:19,760
Because I was still in shock back then.

57
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:35,920
- Hey. What are you doing?
- Don't move.

58
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:51,720
Rachen is really observant.

59
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:53,880
He pays more attention to you than I do.

60
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:56,080
That's true.

61
00:06:57,080 --> 00:06:58,080
Hey, wait.

62
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:00,600
You're not even trying
to spare my feelings?

63
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:08,200
Hang in there.

64
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:14,360
We all have flaws we need to work on.

65
00:07:15,280 --> 00:07:16,480
Don't overthink it.

66
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:19,520
I'm not deducting points
from your point-collecting card.

67
00:07:35,440 --> 00:07:37,520
Come on, handsome.

68
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:41,600
I don't want to be some princess who needs
a prince to take care of her all the time.

69
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,040
But I want to take care of you.

70
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,800
Open the door!

71
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:07,640
Open it right now. Open it.

72
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,480
Open it. Hey.

73
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:12,200
Open the door now.
I know someone's out there.

74
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:13,240
Open the door now.

75
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:16,600
Mom, help me.

76
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:19,440
Mrs. Mook is handling the case for you.

77
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:21,200
Yongyut?

78
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:23,360
You dare lock me in here?

79
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:24,800
You're getting back at me
for your daughter?

80
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:28,520
Open it. How dare you lock me up?
I'll tell Mom.

81
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:30,640
Yongyut!

82
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:33,600
This was Mrs. Mook's order.

83
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:36,200
And no one is allowed
to open the door for you.

84
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,360
Yongyut!

85
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:40,559
You idiot! Open the door!

86
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:51,880
Why is she suddenly quiet?

87
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:55,800
- Watch her. I'm going to rest.
- Yes.

88
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:00,880
Mr. Yongyut, come listen.

89
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:08,840
Is she faking it?

90
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:11,720
She has migraines. When they get bad,

91
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:14,600
she vomits and sometimes even faints.

92
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:21,640
If Mrs. Mook finds out
that we let her get sick…

93
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:33,040
- Ms. Mika.
- Ms. Mika.

94
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,600
- Ms. Mika.
- Are you alright?

95
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:37,200
Yongyut, you dare lock me up?

96
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:39,080
- Ms. Mika.
- You filthy leech. I hate you.

97
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:41,000
You're just as dirty as your daughter.
I hate you.

98
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:42,880
I hate you. I hate your daughter.

99
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:45,640
- Ms. Mika, stop!
- Let go, Yongyut!

100
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:48,960
Ms. Mika!

101
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:54,160
Damn it.

102
00:09:58,880 --> 00:10:00,160
- Where do you think you're going?
- Mom…

103
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:03,640
How could you lock me up like that?

104
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:05,120
I'm not a pet.

105
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:07,400
I'm your daughter.

106
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:10,440
It's because you're my daughter
that I had to lock you up like that.

107
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,520
You never listen to me.

108
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,840
How many times have I warned you
not to cause trouble?

109
00:10:18,760 --> 00:10:20,200
Have you ever listened?

110
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:23,680
Or do you really want to end up in prison?

111
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:27,200
No. You'd never let me go to prison, Mom.

112
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:29,120
If you don't listen to me

113
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,960
and keep acting like this,

114
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:34,600
then I'll have to let someone else
teach you a lesson.

115
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:43,200
No way. If I go to prison,

116
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:45,440
you'll be the one who loses everything.

117
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,480
People will curse you,

118
00:10:47,560 --> 00:10:50,440
say you raised your child badly.

119
00:10:50,520 --> 00:10:54,080
Some might even think
you were involved too.

120
00:10:54,160 --> 00:10:57,040
Your career will be ruined.

121
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:59,240
Your reputation will be destroyed.

122
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:02,560
You won't allow that.

123
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:06,120
So don't make this a big deal.

124
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:08,720
Use your money. Use your power.

125
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:11,480
Close this case quickly for me.

126
00:11:12,680 --> 00:11:14,320
Before I lose my patience.

127
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:28,320
Ms. Mika…

128
00:11:29,680 --> 00:11:30,880
hit me.

129
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:38,360
I told you to take good care of Mika.
You can't even do that.

130
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:40,040
Why are you so useless?!

131
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:41,840
Get out of my house!

132
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:44,400
Get out! Get out!

133
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:45,720
Get out!

134
00:11:57,080 --> 00:11:58,480
I can't take it anymore.

135
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,200
Why are you here?

136
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:14,000
I went to see Uncle Rat.

137
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:16,120
I asked for forgiveness.

138
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:19,760
And did my dad wake up
and accept your apology?

139
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:27,240
I'm truly sorry, Rut.

140
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:29,480
So what?

141
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:33,560
You want to bow to me too?

142
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:36,800
Come in here. Come in here and see me.

143
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:39,000
I'll stick my foot out for you to bow to.

144
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:41,520
I wronged your family.

145
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:43,480
I really do feel guilty.

146
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:45,880
But your being in there,

147
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:48,400
you have to admit
that it's because of what you did.

148
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:51,440
So you're not sorry at all?

149
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:54,360
And you?
How long are you going to blame everyone?

150
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:56,400
You live your life focused on revenge.

151
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:59,720
You spend every breath on the people
you hate. Do you think it's worth it?

152
00:12:59,800 --> 00:13:01,080
It is.

153
00:13:01,160 --> 00:13:03,360
Ever since my parents died,

154
00:13:03,920 --> 00:13:05,480
my life's been hell.

155
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:08,840
Watching you all fall apart heals me.

156
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:11,120
When I saw your father die,

157
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:14,360
I was so damn happy.

158
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:18,720
Happy?

159
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:23,200
Were you really happy?
Because I don't see it.

160
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:26,000
Think it through.

161
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:29,120
Living like this, do you think
your parents would be happy?

162
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:31,840
Stop talking about my parents!

163
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:36,080
You didn't do it alone, did you?

164
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:37,840
What?

165
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:40,400
Who did you have call Petch
to hire him for that job?

166
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:48,280
You still don't know? I'm not the only one

167
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:49,640
who hates you.

168
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:56,360
Even if I'm in here,

169
00:13:56,880 --> 00:13:59,800
I can still drag you down into Hell.
Just watch.

170
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:09,560
You already have someone
in your mind, don't you?

171
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:10,520
Pakbung, of course.

172
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:13,560
Not like that. I meant
the person you suspect worked with Rut.

173
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:17,440
I have someone in mind.
But I'm not sure yet.

174
00:14:25,920 --> 00:14:26,840
Da.

175
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:31,680
I knew that you'd come visit Lee.

176
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:34,080
Can I talk to you for a moment?

177
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:43,920
Say it here.

178
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:48,160
Mr. Rachen and Pakbung

179
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:51,120
think I'm the one
who called and hired Mr. Petch.

180
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:52,880
And did you do it?

181
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:54,920
I don't know anything, Trai.

182
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:58,080
I don't even have his number.
How could I call him?

183
00:14:58,160 --> 00:15:01,120
If you don't believe me,
you can check my phone.

184
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:03,240
No need.

185
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:10,200
- You believe me, right?
- I already asked Rut about it.

186
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:13,200
Huh?

187
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:18,440
What did you ask him?

188
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:21,320
What did he tell you?

189
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:29,440
Da.

190
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:32,240
Out of respect for what we used to be,

191
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:36,800
I'll give you a lump sum,
enough for you to get back on your feet.

192
00:15:36,880 --> 00:15:39,080
But you have to move out of my house.

193
00:15:39,160 --> 00:15:41,720
You have one month.
That should be more than enough.

194
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:43,920
Why?

195
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:47,280
Because of Rut? What did he tell you?

196
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:49,560
Don't believe him, Trai.

197
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:52,040
He's the murderer who killed your father.

198
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:54,440
He's trying to mess with your head.
Don't believe him,

199
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:56,280
- Trai.
- Rut didn't tell me anything.

200
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:59,760
But how you're acting now
told me everything.

201
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:03,240
I don't want this to go to the police.

202
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:05,400
But if you don't stop,

203
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:07,880
I won't be able to help you anymore.

204
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:23,080
Dad! Wow.

205
00:16:23,160 --> 00:16:24,880
You came on the perfect day.

206
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:27,000
How did you know I just finished my exams?

207
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:31,800
Dad.

208
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:34,680
What happened to you?

209
00:16:35,920 --> 00:16:37,120
Pakbung!

210
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:39,520
What is it, Kanah?

211
00:16:46,120 --> 00:16:47,600
Mika hurt me.

212
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:03,520
It's not deep, from what I can see.

213
00:17:04,560 --> 00:17:07,240
But if you want to go to the hospital…

214
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:09,000
It's fine.

215
00:17:10,040 --> 00:17:11,680
As long as you take care of it,

216
00:17:12,319 --> 00:17:13,200
that's enough.

217
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:24,480
Does it hurt, Dad?

218
00:17:29,640 --> 00:17:31,360
I cause problems for you guys.

219
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:33,960
But when I have problems,

220
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:36,240
I come running back to you.

221
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:41,000
Even though I'm the one

222
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:43,560
who abandoned you,

223
00:17:46,280 --> 00:17:49,120
I still have the nerve to come back
and make you take care of me.

224
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:55,240
I really am a terrible person.

225
00:17:59,040 --> 00:18:02,160
I don't know what demon
possessed me back then.

226
00:18:05,560 --> 00:18:06,920
I'm sorry.

227
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:10,240
I'm sorry.

228
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:14,280
So, what did you do

229
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,600
to end up getting…

230
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:20,400
A trash bin to my head.

231
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:22,600
Yeah. That.

232
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:28,160
Or did Mika hurt you

233
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:30,400
because of me?

234
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:33,560
No.

235
00:18:35,400 --> 00:18:37,440
Mika has a bad temper,

236
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:39,160
just like her mother.

237
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,880
When she's upset, she turns to violence.

238
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:45,320
Being there, I wasn't any different

239
00:18:46,120 --> 00:18:48,400
from the trash bin she swung at my head.

240
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:50,560
Just something to take her anger out on.

241
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:52,760
Worthless.

242
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:57,280
I think I'm going to resign.

243
00:18:58,840 --> 00:18:59,960
Resign?

244
00:19:01,360 --> 00:19:02,520
I'm tired.

245
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:05,640
I get older every day.

246
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,960
And I have less time every day.

247
00:19:10,360 --> 00:19:11,960
I want to spend what time I have left

248
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:14,200
with people who love me.

249
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:30,120
Can I come back and live here?

250
00:19:38,320 --> 00:19:40,800
Yes. Yes, Dad, of course.

251
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:42,040
Come live with us.

252
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:48,000
Bung, please let Dad come live with us.

253
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:56,040
I'm going to work.

254
00:19:58,160 --> 00:19:59,520
Going to work now?

255
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:02,960
Then you sleep here, okay?

256
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:07,160
But Pakbung…

257
00:20:08,280 --> 00:20:09,880
She didn't kick you out, did she?

258
00:20:31,840 --> 00:20:33,160
You're thinking about your dad?

259
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:35,640
Kanah reported to you, didn't he?

260
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:40,000
I installed CCTV in your room.
Did you forget already?

261
00:20:41,480 --> 00:20:43,680
So you've been spying on me?

262
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:47,240
Pervert.

263
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:49,760
Kanah called me.

264
00:20:50,360 --> 00:20:51,280
He's worried about you.

265
00:20:54,560 --> 00:20:57,680
You don't want your dad to move back in?

266
00:20:59,200 --> 00:21:00,160
I don't know.

267
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:02,680
That means you want him to stay.

268
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:04,520
Well…

269
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:07,960
I don't know that either.

270
00:21:09,080 --> 00:21:10,800
Honestly, you do know.

271
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:12,360
You just don't want to admit it.

272
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:17,080
When I found out Mika hit him…

273
00:21:19,560 --> 00:21:21,160
I felt a little satisfied.

274
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:24,160
But when I saw how sad he looked,

275
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:27,160
I felt awful.

276
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:29,240
What am I supposed to do?

277
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:32,840
Then let me ask you something simple.

278
00:21:33,880 --> 00:21:36,800
If these moments were the last ones
you and your dad ever shared,

279
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:38,240
what would you choose?

280
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:41,560
Being together
or going your separate ways?

281
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:45,600
I don't know.

282
00:21:46,760 --> 00:21:50,120
It's okay. If you can't choose
right now, that's fine.

283
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:52,480
But I want you to know…

284
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:55,600
"the last time"
happens faster than you think.

285
00:21:57,840 --> 00:21:59,280
Look at me and my dad.

286
00:22:04,320 --> 00:22:06,360
If I don't want him to go,

287
00:22:07,560 --> 00:22:09,640
but I'm not ready to talk to him…

288
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:12,320
what should I do?

289
00:22:19,560 --> 00:22:22,240
I think I have a way.

290
00:22:31,120 --> 00:22:31,960
Niu.

291
00:22:32,480 --> 00:22:36,040
My workplace was giving out free medicine,
so I brought some for you.

292
00:23:00,520 --> 00:23:03,120
Well,

293
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:06,240
I bought this for my grandma,
but she wouldn't eat it.

294
00:23:06,320 --> 00:23:07,600
You can have it.

295
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:15,960
Oh? Where is she going?

296
00:23:16,040 --> 00:23:17,480
I don't know either, Dad.

297
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:21,880
Wait, wait.

298
00:23:22,480 --> 00:23:23,480
Let me see that.

299
00:23:26,920 --> 00:23:29,840
This is kaeng moo chamuang.
How did you know I like this?

300
00:23:31,640 --> 00:23:33,360
I didn't know, Dad.

301
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:39,040
Does Pakbung know?

302
00:23:39,120 --> 00:23:42,280
Of course. When she was little,
we used to eat it together all the time.

303
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,960
Everything was delivered.
No one suspected a thing.

304
00:23:56,480 --> 00:23:58,640
Mission accomplished.

305
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:05,280
You sure it wasn't suspicious?

306
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:07,080
- Not at all.
- Not at all.

307
00:24:09,080 --> 00:24:10,160
Do you feel better now?

308
00:24:10,920 --> 00:24:13,200
Yeah… a bit.

309
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:15,560
Thank you, Mr. Trai.

310
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:22,120
I'll give you one extra good-kid star.

311
00:24:25,280 --> 00:24:26,800
Thanks, Pakbung.

312
00:24:26,880 --> 00:24:29,160
It's nothing. Just some stickers.

313
00:24:35,560 --> 00:24:39,120
That famous kaeng moo chamuang
from Banglamphu I used to take you to eat…

314
00:24:39,200 --> 00:24:40,280
it still tastes just as good, right?

315
00:24:41,840 --> 00:24:45,320
And the medicine…
That was you too, wasn't it?

316
00:24:46,120 --> 00:24:48,760
Why didn't you bring it yourself?
Shy or something?

317
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:51,440
Shy? About what? Who's shy?

318
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:53,520
Okay, okay, not shy.

319
00:24:54,160 --> 00:24:57,960
- You free? Come help prepare Dad's room.
- I'm not going.

320
00:25:02,440 --> 00:25:04,600
My leg still hurts.

321
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:08,720
Then I'll go help.

322
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:09,920
You can just come cheer me on.

323
00:25:11,600 --> 00:25:15,000
Please? Please.

324
00:25:17,720 --> 00:25:18,680
Fine.

325
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:22,240
Only because you asked.

326
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:32,840
- Go.
- What?

327
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:48,960
Thanks.

328
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:56,160
Were we that obvious?

329
00:25:56,240 --> 00:25:58,360
No way. How did he know?

330
00:25:58,440 --> 00:26:00,000
Right? I was slick.

331
00:26:00,080 --> 00:26:02,560
I was slick too. How did he know?

332
00:26:03,160 --> 00:26:05,080
- It was Pakbung.
- Yeah. She gave it away.

333
00:26:05,160 --> 00:26:06,800
Totally obvious.

334
00:26:06,880 --> 00:26:09,280
- Right. But we were so slick.
- Yes.

335
00:26:20,520 --> 00:26:22,320
This isn't your job.

336
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:24,480
Where's Yongyut?

337
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:28,560
Well, you fired him, ma'am.

338
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:32,320
I've tried to fire him many times,
but he's never listened.

339
00:26:34,440 --> 00:26:36,200
Now he suddenly does?

340
00:26:43,960 --> 00:26:45,160
I'm completely wiped out.

341
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:50,440
It's a small room…

342
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:54,120
but it feels really comfortable.

343
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:03,720
Pakbung, I'm done setting up the room.
Do you want to take a look?

344
00:27:05,880 --> 00:27:09,400
- Where are Kanah and Mr. Trai?
- They went to buy food. Kanah was hungry.

345
00:27:10,440 --> 00:27:12,640
Oh. No one told me.

346
00:27:12,720 --> 00:27:14,280
Are you hungry too, Pakbung?

347
00:27:15,120 --> 00:27:18,200
What do you want to eat?
Tell me. I'll go buy it for you.

348
00:27:22,120 --> 00:27:23,560
You don't have to pamper me so much.

349
00:27:25,240 --> 00:27:28,080
I'm not your precious Mika.

350
00:27:37,400 --> 00:27:39,480
It's a good thing that you're not.

351
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:44,680
I never knew…

352
00:27:46,160 --> 00:27:47,840
how lucky I was…

353
00:27:49,880 --> 00:27:52,040
to have you and Kanah as my children.

354
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:58,960
But you two were unlucky
to have a father like me.

355
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:04,600
I threw away
the most valuable thing in my life

356
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:06,520
for money.

357
00:28:07,280 --> 00:28:08,440
And money…

358
00:28:10,240 --> 00:28:12,560
just kept making me
more worthless every day.

359
00:28:18,760 --> 00:28:21,440
I don't deserve to ask you
to forgive me, Pakbung.

360
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:24,520
But I want to thank you

361
00:28:25,280 --> 00:28:27,240
for still giving me a chance

362
00:28:28,840 --> 00:28:29,840
to come back.

363
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:37,720
I'm going to find Kanah and Mr. Trai.

364
00:28:37,800 --> 00:28:40,640
- Wait, Pakbung. Ouch!
- Hey, Dad!

365
00:28:45,400 --> 00:28:46,280
Dad?

366
00:28:48,840 --> 00:28:50,440
Did you just call me Dad?

367
00:28:51,320 --> 00:28:53,600
Did you really call me Dad?

368
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:56,280
I didn't imagine that, right?

369
00:28:59,240 --> 00:29:00,880
Oh, Pakbung.

370
00:29:02,800 --> 00:29:03,800
Come here, let me hug you.

371
00:29:19,040 --> 00:29:20,400
Why are you hugging me?

372
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:24,240
- They'll hear us.
- Yeah, I know.

373
00:29:33,120 --> 00:29:34,800
I don't believe Rut acted alone.

374
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:38,080
Mrs. Mookmanee has to be involved,
at least with the shares.

375
00:29:39,720 --> 00:29:43,040
I already checked.
Mrs. Mookmanee is very careful.

376
00:29:43,120 --> 00:29:45,400
Even though we know
she used nominees to buy up shares,

377
00:29:45,480 --> 00:29:48,360
we don't have any concrete evidence
or documents to take legal action.

378
00:29:50,600 --> 00:29:53,480
But if we let this continue,
Mrs. Mookmanee will gain more power.

379
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:56,480
We need another way
to reduce her influence.

380
00:30:00,520 --> 00:30:01,480
What way?

381
00:30:14,880 --> 00:30:16,520
You're teaming up with Trai.

382
00:30:17,560 --> 00:30:18,640
What are you planning?

383
00:30:20,160 --> 00:30:22,640
If you'd elaborate,

384
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:24,680
I might understand what you mean better.

385
00:30:27,920 --> 00:30:29,880
I've noticed you
meeting Trai quite often lately.

386
00:30:30,560 --> 00:30:33,680
Oh, that's about handling Rut's case.

387
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:42,080
Then why did you investigate me?

388
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:44,920
I didn't get where I am today by luck.

389
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:47,240
If you plan to do
something behind my back,

390
00:30:47,320 --> 00:30:48,520
if you plan to stab me in the back,

391
00:30:49,600 --> 00:30:51,200
do it cleanly.

392
00:30:51,280 --> 00:30:52,560
Don't let me catch you.

393
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:57,360
I know you're concerned about me,

394
00:30:57,440 --> 00:30:59,560
that's why you have people
watching me all the time.

395
00:30:59,640 --> 00:31:02,720
But have you ever considered that
the reason I met Trai

396
00:31:03,320 --> 00:31:04,360
is because

397
00:31:05,320 --> 00:31:07,360
I want him to trust me,

398
00:31:08,360 --> 00:31:09,440
for us?

399
00:31:11,080 --> 00:31:12,200
I got this position

400
00:31:12,720 --> 00:31:14,640
because of you, Mrs. Mookmanee.

401
00:31:18,400 --> 00:31:21,240
Why would I destroy someone
who helped me get here?

402
00:31:24,560 --> 00:31:26,040
So you're planning to be a mole for me?

403
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:29,040
What did you find out?

404
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:33,360
Trai plans to use Mika

405
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:35,920
to bring you down.

406
00:31:45,400 --> 00:31:47,720
Their lawyer just sent this.

407
00:31:47,800 --> 00:31:49,040
They want to negotiate.

408
00:31:52,160 --> 00:31:55,400
If I drop the charges against Mika,
they'll withdraw the lawsuit

409
00:31:55,480 --> 00:31:58,120
where they demanded 20 million baht
in damages from Petch.

410
00:31:58,720 --> 00:32:00,200
They're offering you more money too.

411
00:32:00,800 --> 00:32:01,720
Will you accept?

412
00:32:02,760 --> 00:32:03,760
What do you think, Petch?

413
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:10,720
I don't really want trouble with anyone.

414
00:32:10,800 --> 00:32:13,920
But if you won't back down,

415
00:32:14,880 --> 00:32:16,040
I…

416
00:32:18,080 --> 00:32:19,320
can fight.

417
00:32:25,640 --> 00:32:27,120
You told Mrs. Mookmanee?

418
00:32:29,160 --> 00:32:30,880
For God's sake.
I shouldn't have trusted you.

419
00:32:31,880 --> 00:32:33,560
And you too, Pakbung.

420
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:35,800
How could you give in so easily?
That's not like you at all.

421
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:38,280
Mrs. Mookmanee used Petch as leverage.

422
00:32:38,360 --> 00:32:39,560
I felt sorry for him.

423
00:32:42,480 --> 00:32:43,760
Sorry for Petch?

424
00:32:43,840 --> 00:32:46,280
Or were you more interested
in the extra money?

425
00:32:46,360 --> 00:32:47,480
Trai.

426
00:32:47,560 --> 00:32:49,840
Pakbung chose the best option
for everyone involved.

427
00:32:49,920 --> 00:32:51,040
Best what?

428
00:32:52,120 --> 00:32:54,480
Pakbung, don't you know

429
00:32:54,560 --> 00:32:57,600
I planned to use Mika
to take Mrs. Mookmanee down?

430
00:32:57,680 --> 00:32:59,760
You gave in this easily.
Who's supposed to help me now?

431
00:33:00,760 --> 00:33:02,760
So, you're only worried about yourself.

432
00:33:03,360 --> 00:33:04,720
You're as money hungry as ever.

433
00:33:07,600 --> 00:33:08,680
I care about money.

434
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:10,520
And you only care about yourself.

435
00:33:12,480 --> 00:33:14,120
There's nothing left for us to talk about.

436
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:17,840
Pakbung. Pakbung.

437
00:33:35,360 --> 00:33:38,840
<i>I care about money.</i>
<i>And you only care about yourself.</i>

438
00:33:38,920 --> 00:33:40,400
<i>There's nothing left for us to talk about.</i>

439
00:33:41,320 --> 00:33:43,520
<i>Pakbung. Pakbung.</i>

440
00:33:45,080 --> 00:33:47,720
Trai brought this on himself,
choosing that girl.

441
00:33:48,320 --> 00:33:50,000
Pakbung is just like her father.

442
00:33:50,720 --> 00:33:51,720
They can be bought with money.

443
00:33:53,920 --> 00:33:57,080
Now, Trai only worries about her.
He doesn't pay attention to anything else.

444
00:33:58,240 --> 00:34:00,960
He'll probably stop
bothering you for a while.

445
00:34:01,960 --> 00:34:03,120
That's enough for me.

446
00:34:04,160 --> 00:34:05,960
Now I know where I went wrong,

447
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:09,800
and I'll seal my own leaks.

448
00:34:10,800 --> 00:34:13,320
After this, Trai won't have
anything left to use against me.

449
00:34:20,760 --> 00:34:22,400
EVERYONE'S IN THE MEETING
EXCEPT MRS. MOOK AND MR. RACHEN

450
00:34:23,199 --> 00:34:25,600
We have a board meeting?

451
00:34:25,679 --> 00:34:26,840
Why didn't I know about this?

452
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:38,199
Mrs. Mookmanee, all the executives
are already in the meeting room.

453
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:40,120
You should go right away.

454
00:34:47,280 --> 00:34:48,159
Trai,

455
00:34:48,679 --> 00:34:50,000
what trouble are you causing this time?

456
00:34:51,400 --> 00:34:53,719
I haven't named the agenda yet.

457
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:55,239
What do you think?

458
00:34:57,240 --> 00:34:59,880
Agenda point to remove Mrs. Mookmanee?

459
00:35:02,320 --> 00:35:04,200
Pakbung already signed
an agreement with me.

460
00:35:04,280 --> 00:35:06,880
If you try to use Mika to discredit me,

461
00:35:08,080 --> 00:35:09,400
I won't spare your girlfriend either.

462
00:35:09,480 --> 00:35:11,320
Oh, I know.

463
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:13,320
But that's not why I'm here.

464
00:35:14,200 --> 00:35:15,440
Mr. Kasem, please.

465
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:18,440
This is Mr. Kasem,

466
00:35:18,960 --> 00:35:20,800
a minority shareholder

467
00:35:20,880 --> 00:35:23,160
I contacted to buy back shares.

468
00:35:23,240 --> 00:35:25,240
Turns out he didn't even know
he owned any shares.

469
00:35:27,200 --> 00:35:30,480
That's right. Someone paid me
and used my information.

470
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:33,600
That's him. He said, "It was
all taken care of, Mrs. Mookmanee."

471
00:35:36,280 --> 00:35:38,680
So you really used nominees
to buy up Be Rich shares?

472
00:35:40,920 --> 00:35:44,480
Just because someone says something,
you believe it just like that?

473
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:46,960
You don't have to believe me.

474
00:35:47,560 --> 00:35:49,880
But you probably already know
how Mrs. Mookmanee is.

475
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:51,720
Trai.

476
00:35:54,920 --> 00:35:56,880
Some of you may think

477
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:59,880
it doesn't matter
who the major shareholder is,

478
00:35:59,960 --> 00:36:02,000
as long as dividends keep coming.

479
00:36:02,080 --> 00:36:03,160
But don't forget,

480
00:36:03,240 --> 00:36:06,120
someone who resorts to doing anything
for their own benefit

481
00:36:06,720 --> 00:36:08,480
doesn't care about the greater good.

482
00:36:09,080 --> 00:36:12,040
Do you really want someone like this
to have power over you?

483
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:15,560
But two years ago,
when the company was in trouble,

484
00:36:15,640 --> 00:36:17,720
banks affiliated with Mrs. Mookmanee

485
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:19,960
injected capital and supported us.

486
00:36:20,560 --> 00:36:23,160
Exactly. Without my money,

487
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:25,240
you think Be Rich would have survived?

488
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:29,120
Sky's the limit now.

489
00:36:29,200 --> 00:36:30,760
There are no borders anymore.

490
00:36:33,280 --> 00:36:36,200
You're not the only one who can help us.

491
00:36:47,360 --> 00:36:49,760
I'd like to introduce everyone to Mr. Park

492
00:36:50,640 --> 00:36:52,040
from Beyond Taehan Group.

493
00:36:52,640 --> 00:36:55,040
He's interested in investing in Be Rich.

494
00:36:55,120 --> 00:36:56,320
Hello, Mr. Park.

495
00:36:57,280 --> 00:36:59,560
Thank you

496
00:36:59,640 --> 00:37:01,240
for honoring Be Rich

497
00:37:01,880 --> 00:37:03,080
by joining today's meeting.

498
00:37:03,160 --> 00:37:04,080
Yes.

499
00:37:04,160 --> 00:37:06,680
Hello. My name is Park Jae Jung.

500
00:37:06,760 --> 00:37:08,440
It's a pleasure to meet everyone today.

501
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:21,560
How do you even know
someone of this level?

502
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:27,920
He pushed me

503
00:37:28,000 --> 00:37:30,640
into investor circles from a young age.

504
00:37:31,160 --> 00:37:34,120
So when it comes to connections,
I'm pretty good at them.

505
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:37,040
We party together often.

506
00:37:38,200 --> 00:37:40,040
We're very close.

507
00:37:42,120 --> 00:37:43,200
Confused, huh?

508
00:37:44,800 --> 00:37:46,840
Do you want me to translate?

509
00:37:49,960 --> 00:37:53,520
He said we party together a lot,
that's why we're close.

510
00:37:55,800 --> 00:37:56,840
Yeah.

511
00:38:06,480 --> 00:38:07,760
Mom.

512
00:38:08,680 --> 00:38:11,760
How did it go? Did the board
take interest in the new shareholder?

513
00:38:12,480 --> 00:38:14,040
They still feel
they have to show me respect.

514
00:38:15,320 --> 00:38:17,320
So that means Be Rich is still ours.

515
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:19,440
Only for now.

516
00:38:19,520 --> 00:38:22,640
If they get a new offer that's better,

517
00:38:23,280 --> 00:38:26,080
they'll betray us anytime.

518
00:38:27,800 --> 00:38:28,960
It's strange.

519
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:31,800
You're usually quick to catch things.

520
00:38:31,880 --> 00:38:34,640
How did you not know
what Trai was planning this time?

521
00:38:39,400 --> 00:38:41,080
The reason I slipped up

522
00:38:42,080 --> 00:38:45,160
is because I was busy
cleaning up the mess you created.

523
00:38:47,680 --> 00:38:50,080
So it's my fault again?

524
00:38:52,040 --> 00:38:55,000
You never make mistakes, right, Mom?

525
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:56,040
Mika.

526
00:38:57,560 --> 00:38:59,200
I think

527
00:38:59,280 --> 00:39:01,320
Rachen is the one working with Trai.

528
00:39:02,120 --> 00:39:04,920
And you made a huge mistake

529
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:06,320
trusting him.

530
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:23,920
To Mr. Trai's victory!

531
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:27,280
Yeah!

532
00:39:27,360 --> 00:39:28,960
We haven't won yet.

533
00:39:30,240 --> 00:39:32,400
But you did shake Mrs. Mookmanee.

534
00:39:32,480 --> 00:39:34,200
That deserves a celebration.

535
00:39:34,280 --> 00:39:35,800
- Cheers!
- Wait, wait.

536
00:39:36,400 --> 00:39:38,640
You just got out of the hospital.
How can you drink?

537
00:39:38,720 --> 00:39:40,160
Your wound hasn't even healed.

538
00:39:41,720 --> 00:39:42,720
It's just punch.

539
00:39:43,320 --> 00:39:46,440
Still. It's sweet.
That's not good for wounds.

540
00:39:47,240 --> 00:39:48,120
I'll drink it for you.

541
00:39:53,880 --> 00:39:56,960
I can't even tell if you're worried
about me or just greedy.

542
00:39:57,040 --> 00:39:57,920
Two glasses?

543
00:39:59,680 --> 00:40:01,800
Here. Eat. So you'll stop talking.

544
00:40:02,840 --> 00:40:07,520
Hey. If you want to take care of him,
do it a little more gently.

545
00:40:10,520 --> 00:40:11,880
If I finish chewing,

546
00:40:12,880 --> 00:40:13,880
can you feed me another bite?

547
00:40:16,600 --> 00:40:18,080
Aw. Come on.

548
00:40:20,560 --> 00:40:21,880
It's hot!

549
00:40:21,960 --> 00:40:23,000
Prarop! It's hot!

550
00:40:24,280 --> 00:40:26,000
- Prarop!
- I'm just worried about you.

551
00:40:26,600 --> 00:40:28,080
You're jealous.

552
00:40:29,480 --> 00:40:30,400
Was it good?

553
00:40:31,080 --> 00:40:32,160
Rachen.

554
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:39,400
I can't believe you actually came.

555
00:40:40,760 --> 00:40:41,960
Hey.

556
00:40:42,040 --> 00:40:44,280
If I'd known other people were here,
I wouldn't have come.

557
00:40:44,360 --> 00:40:46,600
What other people? They're all friends.

558
00:40:46,680 --> 00:40:47,920
- It's hot.
- Come on.

559
00:40:49,840 --> 00:40:50,880
- Hello, Mr. Rachen.
- Hello.

560
00:40:50,960 --> 00:40:53,320
- Hello.
- Please have a seat.

561
00:40:54,680 --> 00:40:56,000
Thank you.

562
00:40:57,600 --> 00:40:58,800
Please.

563
00:40:59,320 --> 00:41:01,520
Normally, I charge 500 per person.

564
00:41:01,600 --> 00:41:02,880
But because

565
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:05,520
you're so cool, so smart

566
00:41:05,600 --> 00:41:07,640
to roast Mrs. Mookmanee so good…

567
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:11,480
that I'll feed you for free for life.

568
00:41:14,960 --> 00:41:16,520
Oh, right.

569
00:41:16,600 --> 00:41:19,240
You made Mrs. Mookmanee
drop the lawsuit against Petch, right?

570
00:41:19,800 --> 00:41:22,080
Thank you so much.
Thank you on Petch's behalf too.

571
00:41:22,160 --> 00:41:23,520
- Oh.
- Yes.

572
00:41:23,600 --> 00:41:25,160
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

573
00:41:25,240 --> 00:41:26,320
- Thank you.
- It's fine.

574
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:30,280
I didn't do much.
I just helped distract people

575
00:41:30,800 --> 00:41:32,320
like this guy asked me to.

576
00:41:34,400 --> 00:41:37,800
Pakbung, your acting was really good too

577
00:41:39,120 --> 00:41:40,680
when you pretended to fight with Trai.

578
00:41:45,240 --> 00:41:46,600
Everyone did great.

579
00:41:49,080 --> 00:41:50,120
Come on.

580
00:41:51,480 --> 00:41:53,880
Let's drink for our crew.

581
00:41:56,040 --> 00:41:58,240
Cheers!

582
00:41:58,320 --> 00:42:00,760
- Cheers.
- Just a tap. Oh.

583
00:42:05,600 --> 00:42:06,440
Cheers.

584
00:42:06,520 --> 00:42:09,600
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

585
00:42:11,480 --> 00:42:13,280
Yeah!

586
00:42:13,360 --> 00:42:15,280
- Let's eat.
- Wow.

587
00:42:15,360 --> 00:42:17,960
- Shrimp.
- Papaya salad.

588
00:42:18,040 --> 00:42:18,920
No, no. I'm good.

589
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:21,760
Come on, try it. It's good. Just a bite.

590
00:42:41,880 --> 00:42:42,760
Come in.

591
00:42:44,640 --> 00:42:45,680
What is it, Lee?

592
00:42:49,440 --> 00:42:50,440
Trai.

593
00:42:57,240 --> 00:42:58,160
Da.

594
00:42:59,200 --> 00:43:00,040
You're still here?

595
00:43:02,520 --> 00:43:05,760
Stop kicking me out every two seconds.
I'm packing.

596
00:43:06,800 --> 00:43:07,880
So what do you want?

597
00:43:12,920 --> 00:43:15,120
"Do you miss me? I'm coming to see you."

598
00:43:16,560 --> 00:43:17,720
What is this?

599
00:43:20,200 --> 00:43:21,920
It's Rut's old number.

600
00:43:26,040 --> 00:43:27,000
Mr. Trai.

601
00:43:31,240 --> 00:43:32,160
Look at this.

602
00:43:37,040 --> 00:43:38,760
<i>Do you remember this case?</i>

603
00:43:39,280 --> 00:43:40,120
LEAVE A COMMENT

604
00:43:40,200 --> 00:43:41,840
<i>The one who got arrested was my father.</i>

605
00:43:44,360 --> 00:43:47,720
<i>The court sentenced him to prison</i>
<i>for a fatal car accident.</i>

606
00:43:49,120 --> 00:43:50,560
<i>But you know what?</i>

607
00:43:51,360 --> 00:43:53,200
My father didn't do it.

608
00:43:54,480 --> 00:43:57,000
He was forced to take the blame.

609
00:44:03,040 --> 00:44:04,800
Do you know who the real culprit was?

610
00:44:06,000 --> 00:44:07,520
Do you know Be Rich?

611
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:11,240
That's right.

612
00:44:11,880 --> 00:44:13,680
<i>Mr. Trai Bowornmongkolphong.</i>

613
00:44:14,480 --> 00:44:16,120
<i>He's a rich kid.</i>

614
00:44:17,600 --> 00:44:19,840
<i>He got drunk partying with his friends.</i>

615
00:44:20,440 --> 00:44:22,320
<i>He was the one driving that car.</i>

616
00:44:22,920 --> 00:44:25,880
He's a murderer.
But I can't do anything to him

617
00:44:26,640 --> 00:44:29,400
because he has connections,
because he has power.

618
00:44:30,200 --> 00:44:31,880
He destroyed my family.

619
00:44:32,560 --> 00:44:33,760
THE BAD GUY HAS TO PAY.

620
00:44:33,840 --> 00:44:35,080
WHY DO RICH PEOPLE ALWAYS GET AWAY?

621
00:44:35,160 --> 00:44:36,320
BEING RICH DOESN'T MEAN
HE CAN GET AWAY WITH IT.

622
00:44:36,400 --> 00:44:38,480
Is there anyone who can help me?

623
00:44:41,040 --> 00:44:41,960
Rut…

624
00:44:43,000 --> 00:44:44,120
That's really Rut.

625
00:44:44,200 --> 00:44:45,880
How did he get out?

626
00:45:15,440 --> 00:45:17,520
I've sent it out
to all the major media outlets.

627
00:45:18,360 --> 00:45:22,040
I guarantee Mr. Trai
will get torn apart by the public.

628
00:45:26,280 --> 00:45:28,320
I knew I didn't choose wrong
when I chose you.

629
00:45:32,800 --> 00:45:34,240
At first, I was curious.

630
00:45:34,320 --> 00:45:35,920
You said you weren't doing this for money.

631
00:45:36,960 --> 00:45:38,280
I wondered why you were doing it.

632
00:45:38,880 --> 00:45:41,000
If you'd told me from the start

633
00:45:42,440 --> 00:45:44,000
that you hated Tritot's family,

634
00:45:45,000 --> 00:45:46,680
we could've made a deal a long time ago.

635
00:45:47,320 --> 00:45:48,680
Let me guess.

636
00:45:50,120 --> 00:45:52,640
Trai must be
coming after you over the shares

637
00:45:52,720 --> 00:45:53,960
or maybe…

638
00:45:55,080 --> 00:45:58,160
he already found
a new investor to replace you.

639
00:45:59,240 --> 00:46:00,840
That's why you came to me.

640
00:46:01,880 --> 00:46:04,760
Visiting hours are limited.

641
00:46:06,200 --> 00:46:07,880
So hurry up and tell me your offer.

642
00:46:13,720 --> 00:46:15,720
I want what you have

643
00:46:16,840 --> 00:46:17,920
and no one else does.

644
00:46:21,280 --> 00:46:23,120
Your hatred.

645
00:46:24,920 --> 00:46:27,160
I can make the media
focus on you only as the victim

646
00:46:27,240 --> 00:46:29,800
and not talk about your crimes.

647
00:46:30,400 --> 00:46:31,640
But you must…

648
00:46:34,520 --> 00:46:36,840
help me get Trai out of Be Rich.

649
00:46:39,280 --> 00:46:41,280
I won't let you down.

650
00:46:52,160 --> 00:46:53,760
Mr. Trai, the reporters are everywhere.
What should we do?

651
00:46:56,840 --> 00:46:57,840
I checked already.

652
00:46:57,920 --> 00:47:00,720
The lawyer who bailed Rut out
is Mrs. Mookmanee's person.

653
00:47:02,520 --> 00:47:03,720
I knew this day would come.

654
00:47:03,800 --> 00:47:06,400
Have you thought about
how you're going to deal with it?

655
00:47:11,920 --> 00:47:13,480
MOM

656
00:47:15,520 --> 00:47:16,760
Yes, Mom?

657
00:47:17,440 --> 00:47:20,520
Can you not ask me things right now?
I'm stressed out enough as it is.

658
00:47:28,000 --> 00:47:30,880
Since the reporters are here,
should we just hold a press conference

659
00:47:30,960 --> 00:47:32,120
and say who was the one

660
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:33,960
driving that day?

661
00:47:37,000 --> 00:47:40,120
Why are you looking at me?
This has nothing to do with me.

662
00:47:40,200 --> 00:47:41,240
Da,

663
00:47:42,200 --> 00:47:43,720
I think it's time

664
00:47:44,720 --> 00:47:45,800
we face the truth.

665
00:47:47,320 --> 00:47:51,400
No. Don't slander me. You can't just
dump the blame on me like this.

666
00:47:52,000 --> 00:47:53,520
I didn't do it.

667
00:48:10,320 --> 00:48:12,840
This is your new phone
and a rental apartment.

668
00:48:13,480 --> 00:48:15,160
Mrs. Mookmanee
has prepared everything for you.

669
00:48:15,800 --> 00:48:18,360
If you need anything else,

670
00:48:18,880 --> 00:48:19,800
just let me know.

671
00:48:21,480 --> 00:48:22,440
Thank you.

672
00:48:27,680 --> 00:48:28,560
Rut.

673
00:48:30,040 --> 00:48:32,320
- Mr. Rachen!
- You bastard! How did you get out?!

674
00:48:32,400 --> 00:48:33,840
- Please calm down.
- Let go!

675
00:48:33,920 --> 00:48:36,240
A piece of shit like you
should rot and die in prison.

676
00:48:36,320 --> 00:48:37,800
You killed my father.

677
00:48:37,880 --> 00:48:39,840
I'll never let you go, Rut.

678
00:48:40,360 --> 00:48:43,680
Mr. Rachen, please calm down.

679
00:48:43,760 --> 00:48:45,080
Stop it right now!

680
00:49:00,440 --> 00:49:02,960
Let go of me. Rut, you bastard.

681
00:49:03,040 --> 00:49:05,080
Let go! Let me go!

682
00:49:06,480 --> 00:49:07,720
Mrs. Mookmanee,

683
00:49:07,800 --> 00:49:10,600
you know he killed my father!
So why are you helping him?

684
00:49:11,120 --> 00:49:13,160
Because the people around me
are not trustworthy.

685
00:49:13,240 --> 00:49:15,000
And you think he is?

686
00:49:15,080 --> 00:49:16,720
He just betrayed me.

687
00:49:16,800 --> 00:49:19,760
Rut never worked for
the Bowornmongkolphongs to begin with,

688
00:49:20,520 --> 00:49:22,040
so it can't be called betrayal.

689
00:49:23,520 --> 00:49:24,520
Okay.

690
00:49:29,120 --> 00:49:31,000
I trusted you.

691
00:49:31,080 --> 00:49:34,520
I believed in you completely.
I took care of you!

692
00:49:35,320 --> 00:49:37,760
And you killed my father?!

693
00:49:37,840 --> 00:49:40,000
How could you do this to me?!

694
00:49:40,080 --> 00:49:43,360
I'll kill you, Rut! You bastard! Let go!

695
00:49:43,440 --> 00:49:45,040
Let go!

696
00:49:45,640 --> 00:49:47,760
Let go! Let me go!

697
00:49:58,920 --> 00:50:03,040
I tolerated you
because you used to be a good boss to me.

698
00:50:03,600 --> 00:50:04,600
But now,

699
00:50:05,400 --> 00:50:06,720
your special treatment is over.

700
00:50:14,080 --> 00:50:15,720
From now on,

701
00:50:16,480 --> 00:50:19,600
I'll consider you
as another son of Tritot.

702
00:50:19,680 --> 00:50:22,000
And your life will be ruined too.

703
00:50:34,760 --> 00:50:36,600
I told you from the start

704
00:50:38,480 --> 00:50:39,760
to be on my side.

705
00:51:11,760 --> 00:51:15,080
Everyone has seen it, right?
The stock price dropped immediately.

706
00:51:15,680 --> 00:51:18,640
And Trai has gone silent.
That means the news is true.

707
00:51:19,240 --> 00:51:21,600
Mr. Trai is being discredited
by people with bad intentions.

708
00:51:21,680 --> 00:51:25,480
If he comes out now,
it would be like pouring oil on the fire.

709
00:51:25,560 --> 00:51:27,160
He's good at running away.

710
00:51:28,560 --> 00:51:32,040
He ran from the case before,
and now he's running from responsibility.

711
00:51:33,520 --> 00:51:37,720
I already gave an interview to the press
that the law allows cases to be reopened.

712
00:51:37,800 --> 00:51:41,280
Rut should gather evidence
and file it properly with the court,

713
00:51:41,360 --> 00:51:42,720
then let the law decide,

714
00:51:43,440 --> 00:51:46,040
not play this dirty game
using someone else's hands to attack.

715
00:51:47,520 --> 00:51:49,040
But it doesn't help much.

716
00:51:49,560 --> 00:51:52,560
Our Be Rich page faced so much backlash
that it crashed several times already.

717
00:51:52,640 --> 00:51:54,600
One rotten apple spoils the whole barrel.

718
00:51:55,200 --> 00:51:57,360
As long as Mr. Trai
is still listed as a major shareholder,

719
00:51:57,440 --> 00:51:59,400
Be Rich's reputation
will keep taking damage.

720
00:51:59,480 --> 00:52:02,080
But I believe Be Rich is strong.

721
00:52:02,160 --> 00:52:04,800
We won't be taken down
by news and public opinion that easily.

722
00:52:04,880 --> 00:52:07,160
And why do you think
our foundation is strong?

723
00:52:08,120 --> 00:52:10,040
Isn't it all because of my capital?

724
00:52:11,760 --> 00:52:14,040
I don't like being entangled in scandals.

725
00:52:14,120 --> 00:52:17,600
If you all continue to let Mr. Trai
remain a major shareholder…

726
00:52:20,960 --> 00:52:23,000
then I will withdraw all of my shares.

727
00:52:30,640 --> 00:52:32,880
I already know. Prarop called and told me.

728
00:52:33,720 --> 00:52:35,440
The board's pressuring me
to sell my shares, right?

729
00:52:35,520 --> 00:52:38,400
Yes. And what did your Korean friend say?

730
00:52:38,480 --> 00:52:40,480
Is he still interested
in investing with us?

731
00:52:40,560 --> 00:52:43,240
His parent company
wants to hold off for now

732
00:52:43,320 --> 00:52:44,160
because of the news.

733
00:52:44,240 --> 00:52:47,880
Hey, Trai, I don't know how long
I can hold them off for you.

734
00:52:47,960 --> 00:52:50,720
If Mrs. Mookmanee
threatens to pull her shares again,

735
00:52:50,800 --> 00:52:52,240
the board

736
00:52:52,320 --> 00:52:55,640
might sign together
to remove you from the company.

737
00:52:55,720 --> 00:52:58,280
If that day comes,
I'll give my shares to you.

738
00:52:58,360 --> 00:53:00,000
Don't joke with me.

739
00:53:00,600 --> 00:53:02,160
Don't be too happy yet.

740
00:53:02,680 --> 00:53:04,040
Before that day comes,

741
00:53:05,160 --> 00:53:06,720
I'll clear this up.

742
00:53:07,760 --> 00:53:08,840
And how are you going to do that?

743
00:53:38,400 --> 00:53:39,560
Trai.

744
00:53:40,160 --> 00:53:43,000
You used to hate how my dad
used money to buy everything.

745
00:53:44,640 --> 00:53:46,240
So why did you let yourself
be bought today?

746
00:53:47,400 --> 00:53:50,600
- What?
- I talked to Uncle Rat before, you know.

747
00:53:50,680 --> 00:53:54,440
He was damn proud of his son.
But if he could see you like this today--

748
00:53:54,520 --> 00:53:56,320
Don't you dare talk about my father.

749
00:53:57,720 --> 00:54:00,160
How long are you going to let me
have power over your life?

750
00:54:01,040 --> 00:54:04,200
Until you burn in Hell just like me.

751
00:54:06,360 --> 00:54:08,200
Then try to stay above me.

752
00:54:09,480 --> 00:54:12,600
Be better than me. Be happier than me.

753
00:54:15,040 --> 00:54:16,240
I can do that

754
00:54:17,800 --> 00:54:20,680
by dragging you down lower than me.

755
00:54:23,680 --> 00:54:25,640
And I'll drag Pakbung down with you.

756
00:54:27,280 --> 00:54:28,400
Don't you touch Pakbung.

757
00:54:31,080 --> 00:54:34,520
Both you and Rachen
like her a lot, don't you?

758
00:54:34,600 --> 00:54:36,240
You're competing over her.

759
00:54:36,320 --> 00:54:38,840
I'll take care of her first.
I'll go all the way.

760
00:54:38,920 --> 00:54:41,040
- I'll make that girl forget both of you.
- You bastard!

761
00:54:43,040 --> 00:54:45,160
I'll kiss her. I'll touch her.

762
00:54:45,240 --> 00:54:47,160
I'll grope her. I'll take her--

763
00:54:49,720 --> 00:54:53,040
This is live right now.
High-society heir, Mr. T.,

764
00:54:53,120 --> 00:54:54,920
is attacking the victim at his own home.

765
00:54:55,000 --> 00:54:57,200
You have no right to film this.
Stop filming right now.

766
00:54:58,440 --> 00:55:02,040
Mr. Trai, I'm scared. I'm sorry.

767
00:55:02,120 --> 00:55:04,360
I won't give
any more interviews about you.

768
00:55:05,040 --> 00:55:06,760
I'm sorry, Mr. Trai.

769
00:55:06,840 --> 00:55:08,800
Please don't hurt me. I'm scared.

770
00:55:08,880 --> 00:55:09,800
Please stop filming.

771
00:55:09,880 --> 00:55:11,640
You have no right to record this.
Stop filming.

772
00:55:11,720 --> 00:55:14,320
- Ow, Mr. Trai, my wrist hurts.
- Please stop.

773
00:55:14,400 --> 00:55:15,360
MR. T. ATTACKS THE VICTIM

774
00:55:15,440 --> 00:55:17,200
This is what you meant
by handling it yourself?

775
00:55:18,400 --> 00:55:20,320
Making an even bigger mess like this?

776
00:55:21,800 --> 00:55:23,040
Please don't blame him, sir.

777
00:55:23,120 --> 00:55:25,120
He went to talk to Rut calmly,
hoping he'd come to his senses,

778
00:55:25,200 --> 00:55:26,960
but Rut kept provoking him.

779
00:55:27,040 --> 00:55:28,880
Anyone would've wanted to hit him
given the things he said.

780
00:55:28,960 --> 00:55:32,400
Shut up, Lee. Instead of stopping him,
you encouraged it.

781
00:55:33,000 --> 00:55:34,360
That's why everything
played right into Rut's hands.

782
00:55:34,440 --> 00:55:37,400
I was careless. I didn't think
he'd have reporters waiting.

783
00:55:37,480 --> 00:55:39,280
And you think realizing that now helps?

784
00:55:40,600 --> 00:55:42,080
Where's the one who started all this?

785
00:55:43,400 --> 00:55:45,320
She's still in this house, right?

786
00:55:48,000 --> 00:55:49,480
- I'll go talk to her.
- No, Bro.

787
00:55:50,680 --> 00:55:51,800
I'll talk to her myself.

788
00:55:51,880 --> 00:55:54,040
How long are you going
to let her run away?

789
00:55:54,920 --> 00:55:57,400
She needs to come out
and take responsibility.

790
00:56:30,400 --> 00:56:31,400
Did you miss me?

791
00:56:33,880 --> 00:56:35,560
I've been waiting for you every day.

792
00:56:36,880 --> 00:56:38,360
I thought you might come visit sometime.

793
00:56:38,960 --> 00:56:40,040
I…

794
00:56:40,920 --> 00:56:43,760
I was scared. Everyone's watching me,

795
00:56:43,840 --> 00:56:45,400
accusing me of working with you.

796
00:56:45,480 --> 00:56:47,280
But I didn't sell you out.

797
00:56:49,880 --> 00:56:52,680
Why? Who was it?
Who said something to you?

798
00:56:53,960 --> 00:56:55,040
Trai, right?

799
00:56:56,880 --> 00:56:57,720
Everyone.

800
00:56:58,360 --> 00:56:59,680
I'll take care of it.

801
00:57:00,920 --> 00:57:03,440
Trai. Pakbung.

802
00:57:04,160 --> 00:57:05,720
Rachen.

803
00:57:05,800 --> 00:57:07,400
They love looking down on you.

804
00:57:08,480 --> 00:57:09,640
You…

805
00:57:11,080 --> 00:57:13,400
You're going to kill them?

806
00:57:14,680 --> 00:57:15,640
Not yet.

807
00:57:16,440 --> 00:57:18,040
I have another way that's more fun.

808
00:57:20,200 --> 00:57:22,080
Do you want to have some fun with me?

809
00:57:24,920 --> 00:57:27,320
Da? Is that you?

810
00:57:27,400 --> 00:57:29,040
My mom's coming out.

811
00:57:29,640 --> 00:57:32,200
Please go.
I don't want her to get suspicious.

812
00:57:32,280 --> 00:57:34,520
Please go first.

813
00:57:45,400 --> 00:57:46,680
I missed you.

814
00:57:58,120 --> 00:58:00,600
Da, what's wrong?

815
00:58:00,680 --> 00:58:03,000
What happened? What's wrong, darling?

816
00:58:03,080 --> 00:58:04,000
Da.

817
00:58:06,960 --> 00:58:09,080
- Mom…
- What's wrong?

818
00:58:09,720 --> 00:58:11,920
Did I really do something that wrong?

819
00:58:12,640 --> 00:58:14,040
Why?

820
00:58:15,120 --> 00:58:17,040
Why is everyone ganging up on me?

821
00:58:17,120 --> 00:58:18,800
Why?

822
00:58:18,880 --> 00:58:22,680
- Why, Mom?
- There, there. Calm down.

823
00:58:25,280 --> 00:58:26,640
It's okay. Don't cry.

824
00:58:29,760 --> 00:58:31,080
EVIL PEOPLE'S SCHOOL

825
00:58:31,160 --> 00:58:33,400
It's difficult now.
If this neighborhood doesn't welcome you,

826
00:58:33,480 --> 00:58:34,520
how are you supposed
to open a school here?

827
00:58:34,600 --> 00:58:36,840
<i>Everything started with me,</i>
<i>so it has to end with me.</i>

828
00:58:36,920 --> 00:58:38,480
I need to face the truth.

829
00:58:38,560 --> 00:58:42,080
Don't tell me you're going to admit
that you were the one driving that car.

830
00:58:42,160 --> 00:58:44,080
She forced me to take the blame for you.

831
00:58:44,600 --> 00:58:46,600
I'm really disappointed in you, Pakbung.

832
00:58:48,320 --> 00:58:51,760
You really don't see that Darin
is trying to come back into your life.

833
00:58:51,840 --> 00:58:54,920
We created this problem,
so we have to get through it together.

834
00:58:55,000 --> 00:58:56,840
You won't abandon me, right, Trai?

835
00:58:58,960 --> 00:59:02,040
Say it straight, Trai. Be a man.

836
00:59:02,120 --> 00:59:06,560
Who are you choosing?
Me or your ex? Choose.

837
00:59:12,680 --> 00:59:15,320
Pakbung is my girlfriend.
Why are you getting involved with her?

838
00:59:15,400 --> 00:59:17,480
If you can't take care of Pakbung,

839
00:59:17,560 --> 00:59:18,520
I will.

840
01:00:07,680 --> 01:00:09,680
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
